{"id":116,"parent_id":114,"book_id":9398,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":116,"title":"Romans 2: God Shall Reward Each of Us According to Our Works","subtitle":"","short_title":"Romans 2: God Shall Reward Each of Us According to Our Works","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-romans/romans-2-god-shall-reward-each-of-us-according-to-our-works","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-romans/romans-2-god-shall-reward-each-of-us-according-to-our-works"},[".heading",{"id":"head3","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-romans/romans-2-god-shall-reward-each-of-us-according-to-our-works.head3"},["h1","Romans 2"],[".subtitle","God Shall Reward Each of Us According to Our Works"],[".intro","Have you ever criticized someone for doing something wrong and later caught yourself doing the same thing? That was a common fault among Church members in Paul’s day. Notice Paul’s teachings on the difference between the way we often judge and the way God judges."]],[".bodyBlock",[".",{"id":"f4","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-romans/romans-2-god-shall-reward-each-of-us-according-to-our-works.f4"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/p-112-2.gif"}],[".caption",["p",{"id":"lds-"},["span.emphasis","Jesus Christ, the Righteous Judge"]]]],[".topic",["h2","Understanding the Scriptures"],[".figure",{"id":"f5","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-romans/romans-2-god-shall-reward-each-of-us-according-to-our-works.f5"},["p"],["h2",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rom/2"},"Romans 2"]],["p"],["table",["tbody",["tr",["td",["b","Impenitent"],"(v. 5)"],["td","Unrepentant"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Indignation and wrath"],"(v. 8)"],["td","Fury and anger"],["td"]]]]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rom/2.14-29"},"Romans 2:14–29"],"—“For He Is Not a Jew, Which Is One Outwardly”"],["p.para",{"id":"p24","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-romans/romans-2-god-shall-reward-each-of-us-according-to-our-works.p24"},"Paul taught the Jewish Christians that having the outward signs of righteousness (such as circumcision) meant nothing if a spirit of faith and obedience did not dwell in them. The same is true today. Outward signs of righteousness (such as Church attendance) are not enough. A spirit of faith, love, and obedience must also dwell in our hearts."]]],[".topic",["h2","Studying the Scriptures"],["p.para",{"id":"p25","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-romans/romans-2-god-shall-reward-each-of-us-according-to-our-works.p25"},"Do the following activity as you study",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rom/2"},"Romans 2"],"."],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-a.gif"}],"In Your Own Words"],["p.para",{"id":"p26","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-epistle-of-paul-the-apostle-to-the-romans/romans-2-god-shall-reward-each-of-us-according-to-our-works.p26"},"As you consider what Paul taught about judging others and about the Lord judging each of us, read",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rom/2.1-2,5-11"},"Romans 2:1–2, 5–11"],"and write the main ideas."]]]],[".resources"]]]],"refs":null}
